  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSpecifying `FOUNDRY_SOLC_VERSION` as an env variable or `solc_version` in `foundry.toml` should tell the compiler what solidity version it should use to compile the contracts.\r\n\r\nCurrently this is not the case as forge uses the latest solidity version instead of the specified one.",
